# How to Download and Run FileStack

Follow these steps to get FileStack running on your Windows computer:

---

## 1. Download the Release

1. Go to the [Releases page](https://github.com/Austin9619/FileStack/releases) of this repository.  
2. Find the latest release (e.g., `v1.0`).  
3. Download the ZIP file attached to the release (e.g., `FileStack V1.0.0.zip`).

---

## 2. Extract the ZIP

1. Right-click the downloaded ZIP file.  
2. Choose **Extract Allâ€¦** or use your unzipping tool.  
3. Select a location to extract to (e.g., Desktop or Documents).

> Make sure all files remain together in the same folder.

---

## 3. Run FileStack

1. Open the folder where you extracted the files.  
2. Double-click **`FileStack.exe`** to launch the program.  

---

## 4. Using FileStack

1. Click **Select Folder** to choose the folder you want to organize.  
2. Click **Sort**.  
3. A new folder will appear on your desktop containing the organized files.  
